Pop your #kettle{} on to boil. Halve the @bell pepper{1}(halved) and discard the core and seeds. Chop into small pieces. Trim and thinly slice the @spring onion{1}(thinly sliced). Halve the @red chilli{1/2}(halved lengthways), deseed then finely chop. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all). Zest and halve the @lime{1/2}(zested and halved).

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a large #saucepan{} on medium heat. Add the pepper, garlic, chilli and half the spring onion. Stir and cook for ~{2%minutes}, then add the @red Thai style paste{50%g} and stir together.

> TIP: Add less chilli if you don't like spice!

After ~{1%minute}, pour in the @coconut milk{200%ml} and mix until smooth. Add the @chicken stock paste{10%g} with the @water{400%ml} from your kettle (see ingredients for amount) and bring to a simmer.

Add the @peanut butter{30%g} and a pinch of @?sugar{pinch} to your pan. Simmer gently for ~{10%minutes}. Taste the laksa and add seasoning if you think it needs it - @?salt{}, @?pepper{}, @?sugar{} - whatever suits your taste!

Meanwhile, heat a splash of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the @chicken thigh{210%g}(diced) and lime zest. Season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Stir-fry until cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw chicken and its packaging. The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

When cooked, remove to a #plate{} and cover with #foil{} to keep warm.

When the laksa has been cooking for ~{10%minutes}, add in the @egg noodle nest{2} and @king prawns{150%g} to the sauce. Cook until the noodles are soft enough to eat and the prawns are cooked through, about ~{4%minutes}.

> TIP: The noodles may soak up some of the coconutty liquid. If this is the case, just add a splash of water to get it back to a soupy consistency.

> IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Add the chicken to the #pan{} and simmer until the chicken is piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove from the heat and add half the lime juice. Taste and add @salt{}, @pepper{} and more lime juice if you feel it needs it. Serve in big #bowls{} topped with the coriander and the remaining spring onion. Enjoy!

> Modularity Step: If you've opted to add prawns to your meal, add them to the sauce when you add the noodles and cook for the same amount of time. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw prawns. The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.